#: ../../source/wapt-security/secure-my-wapt-server.rst:17
msgid ""
"By default, all WAPT packages are signed with your private key, which "
"already provides a great level of security. However you can further "
"improve the security of WAPT."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/wapt-security/secure-my-wapt-server.rst:21
msgid "To fully secure your WAPT setup; you will want to do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/wapt-security/secure-my-wapt-server.rst:23
msgid ""
"enable authenticated registration to filter who is authorized to register"
" the device with the WAPT server;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/wapt-security/secure-my-wapt-server.rst:26
msgid ""
"enable https certificate verification on the agents and the console to "
"ensure that the WAPT agents and the WAPT console are connecting to the "
"correct WAPT server;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/wapt-security/secure-my-wapt-server.rst:30
msgid ""
"configure authentication against Active Directory to allow access to the "
"WAPT console only to authorized WAPT admins;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/wapt-security/secure-my-wapt-server.rst:33
msgid ""
"enable Client-Side Certificate Authentication to only allow authenticated"
" devices to access the WAPT server (Note: it is especially important if "
"you want to expose your WAPT server to the outside in a :abbr:`DMZ (De-"
"Militarized Zone)`);"
msgstr ""

